ds-on software&lt;br /&gt;development and testing, typically spending about 75% of time writing code,&lt;br /&gt;conducting code reviews and testing in ongoing sprints, or updating automation&lt;br /&gt;tools&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Drive consistent development&lt;br /&gt;practices, tools, and components across the agile team&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Develop a deep understanding of&lt;br /&gt;relationships with other systems and platforms within the supported domains&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Work with technical product&lt;br /&gt;managers contributing to blueprints, and assisting with annual planning of&lt;br /&gt;feature sets that impact multiple platforms&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify opportunities&lt;br /&gt;for adopting exciting new technology to solve existing needs and future&lt;br /&gt;challenges&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Mentor engineers and may have&lt;br /&gt;management responsibilities for 2-3 engineers&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Perform or direct ongoing&lt;br /&gt;refactoring of configuration and code to drive continuous improvement in code&lt;br /&gt;structure and quality&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Use visualization and other prototyping&lt;br /&gt;techniques to fast-track concepts and design discussions&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Works closely with other&lt;br /&gt;engineers, architects, and project management throughout the course of the&lt;br /&gt;development lifecycle to ensure business objectives are met&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Manages and appropriately escalates delivery&lt;br /&gt;impediments, risks, issues, and changes tied to the product development&lt;br /&gt;initiatives&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;3+ years of software development&lt;br /&gt;experience&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Minimum 2+ years of experience&lt;br /&gt;architecting, designing, programming, and configuring the Salesforce.com&lt;br /&gt;platform and deep functional understanding of its capabilities and limitations&lt;/li&gt;&